laboratory_examinations.findings: Dependent atelectasis in the lung bases. No pleural effusion. Heart normal in size without pericardial effusion. Liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands unremarkable. Kidneys enhance symmetrically without hydronephrosis or hydroureter. Small and large bowel loops normal in caliber. A retrocecal appendix measuring up to 7 mm, with mild periappendiceal fat stranding, suggestive of early tip appendicitis. No perforation or periappendiceal abscess formation. No intra-abdominal adenopathy. Great vessels patent. Bladder, distal ureters, prostate, and rectum unremarkable. Small inguinal and pelvic sidewall nodes do not meet size criteria for adenopathy. No free fluid in pelvis. No focal concerning lesion.
15.0 mg/dL of gram-positive bacteria, within reference range of 6.0 to 20.0 mg/dL.
